FSS :- 
Flexible Storage Sharing (FSS) is an InfoScale feature that allows cluster nodes to access shared storage even when
they do not have direct visibility to the SAN LUNs. In a traditional CVM/CFS environment, every node must be zoned and 
presented with the same storage. With FSS, only a subset of nodes, called storage nodes, require direct storage access. 
Other nodes access the storage through the cluster. This reduces SAN complexity, lowers infrastructure costs,
and is especially useful in cloud and virtualized environments where shared storage visibility may not be available on every 
node. FSS provides the benefits of clustered storage while requiring fewer direct storage connections.
